BUG FIX — Conductor::poll() at lines 71-84 uses old_iter.next() to recover captures from errored panes. This is wrong: old_iter advances sequentially through old_captures, so if pane 0 succeeds and pane 1 errors, old_iter.next() gives old_captures[0] (the first old capture, not the one for pane 1).

File: crates/thermal-conductor/src/conductor.rs

Change lines 71-84:

OLD:
```rust
let old_captures = std::mem::replace(&mut self.captures, Vec::with_capacity(n));
let mut old_iter = old_captures.into_iter();
for (i, opt) in new_captures.into_iter().enumerate() {
    match opt {
        Some(c) => self.captures.push(c),
        None => {
            if let Some(old) = old_iter.next() {
                self.captures.push(old);
            }
            let _ = i;
        }
    }
}
```

NEW:
```rust
// Convert old captures to indexed Vec<Option<PaneCapture>> so we can take
// by index rather than iterating sequentially.
let mut old_indexed: Vec<Option<PaneCapture>> = std::mem::replace(&mut self.captures, Vec::with_capacity(n))
    .into_iter()
    .map(Some)
    .collect();
// Pad to n in case panes were added.
old_indexed.resize_with(n, || None);

for (i, opt) in new_captures.into_iter().enumerate() {
    match opt {
        Some(c) => self.captures.push(c),
        None => {
            if let Some(old) = old_indexed[i].take() {
                self.captures.push(old);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Success criteria: `cargo check -p thermal-conductor` passes.

