BUG FIX — StateDetector::has_error_pattern() at lines 96-108 uses substring matching (`clean.contains(pattern)`). This causes false positives: 'no error found', '0 errors', 'error handling is working', etc. all trigger Error state.

File: crates/thermal-conductor/src/state_detector.rs

Change has_error_pattern() to use whole-word matching via regex or manual word-boundary check.

Simplest fix without adding regex crate — use a word-boundary check function:

```rust
fn has_error_pattern(&self, lines: &[&str]) -> bool {
    let check_lines = if lines.len() > 5 { &lines[lines.len()-5..] } else { lines };
    for line in check_lines {
        let clean = strip_ansi(line);
        for pattern in &self.error_patterns {
            if contains_whole_word(&clean, pattern) {
                return true;
            }
        }
    }
    false
}
```

Add the helper function after has_error_pattern:
```rust
/// Returns true if `text` contains `word` as a whole word (bounded by
/// non-alphanumeric characters or string start/end).
fn contains_whole_word(text: &str, word: &str) -> bool {
    let mut start = 0;
    while let Some(pos) = text[start..].find(word) {
        let abs = start + pos;
        let before_ok = abs == 0 || !text.as_bytes()[abs - 1].is_ascii_alphanumeric();
        let after_ok = abs + word.len() >= text.len()
            || !text.as_bytes()[abs + word.len()].is_ascii_alphanumeric();
        if before_ok && after_ok {
            return true;
        }
        start = abs + 1;
    }
    false
}
```

Success criteria: `cargo check -p thermal-conductor` passes. Manually verify: 'no error found' does NOT trigger, 'error: something failed' DOES trigger, 'Error: panic' DOES trigger.

BUG FIX — WgpuState::render() at lines 114-119 uses hardcoded linear float values for the background color instead of ThermalPalette::BG. Also, ThermalPalette::hex() converts u8 to f32 by dividing by 255.0 but wgpu expects linear (sRGB) values — so sRGB-to-linear conversion is needed.

