BUG FIX — Rect::grid() at line 55-58 divides by cols and rows as f32 without guarding against zero, producing f32::INFINITY tiles when cols=0 or rows=0.

File: crates/thermal-core/src/geometry.rs

OLD (line 55-58):
```rust
pub fn grid(self, cols: usize, rows: usize) -> Vec<Rect> {
    let tw = self.size.width / cols as f32;
    let th = self.size.height / rows as f32;
    (0..rows).flat_map(|r| (0..cols).map(move |c| ...)).collect()
}
```

NEW:
```rust
pub fn grid(self, cols: usize, rows: usize) -> Vec<Rect> {
    if cols == 0 || rows == 0 {
        return vec![];
    }
    let tw = self.size.width / cols as f32;
    let th = self.size.height / rows as f32;
    (0..rows).flat_map(|r| (0..cols).map(move |c| Rect::new(self.origin.x + c as f32 * tw, self.origin.y + r as f32 * th, tw, th))).collect()
}
```

Note: split_horizontal(n) and split_vertical(n) at lines 45-53 already guard `if n == 0 { return vec![]; }` — only grid() is missing this guard.

Success criteria: `cargo check -p thermal-core` passes. `Rect::new(0.0,0.0,100.0,100.0).grid(0,4)` returns empty Vec without panic.

